<paragraph id="8B9898347E54FFD8FF3F7089DD74FA39" blockId="38.[192,1441,931,1474]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FF3F7089DE4FFC40" bold="true" box="[192,337,931,955]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus to 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FDDD7089DC48FC40" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[546,854,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Oxynthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FDDD7089DD8FFC40" box="[546,657,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Oxynthes</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E54FFD8FC9B7089DC87FC40" box="[868,921,931,955]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FC067089DFE2FC27" authority="Herrich-Schaffer, 1869" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1869" genus="Goniloba" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="corusca">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FC067089DBD9FC40" box="[1017,1223,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Goniloba corusca</emphasis>
Herrich-Sch√§ffer, 1869
</taxonomicName>
) combined with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FE3570EEDDECFC27" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[458,754,964,988]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Oeonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FE3570EEDD3AFC20" box="[458,548,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Oeonus</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E54FFD8FCFC70EEDC27FC27" box="[771,825,964,988]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FC5F70EEDA10FC27" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[928,1294,964,988]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Oeonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyste">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FC5F70EEDB5EFC20" box="[928,1088,964,987]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Oeonus pyste</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
) and in the same clade with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FE7470CEDD60FC07" authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[395,638,996,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Lindra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FE7470CEDEFFFC07" box="[395,481,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Lindra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD8FE1770CFDD60FC07" author="Evans" box="[488,638,996,1020]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E54FFD8FD7270CEDDDDFC07" box="[653,707,996,1020]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FCD970CEDB80FC07" authority="Druce, 1876" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1876" box="[806,1182,996,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulius">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FCD970CEDB1AFC07" box="[806,1028,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Carystus simulius</emphasis>
Druce, 1876
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E54FFD8FB4970CEDA12FC07" box="[1206,1292,996,1020]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="39.[192,275,1562,1584]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,215,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[192,1440,213,1528]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 13. Genomic trees of Hesperiina, Pericharini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677261/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FE9B772EDD4EFBE7" authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[356,592,1028,1052]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Orthos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FE9B772EDEA9FBE7" box="[356,439,1028,1052]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Orthos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD8FE43772FDD4EFBE7" author="Evans" box="[444,592,1028,1052]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E54FFD8FDA1772FDD8DFBE6" box="[606,659,1029,1053]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FD0B772EDB96FBE6" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[756,1160,1028,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Eutychide" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orthos">
<emphasis id="B95344267E54FFD8FD0B772EDCA1FBE7" box="[756,959,1028,1052]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Eutychide orthos</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
), which is in a different subtribe (
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E54FFD8FEC9770FDD45FBC6" authority="Mabille 1878" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1878" box="[310,603,1061,1085]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carystina Mabille 1878</taxonomicName>
). Keys to L. 
<quantity id="4CDF35D17E54FFD8FD16770FDC21FBC6" box="[745,831,1061,1085]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.937" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" unit="in" value="15.5">15.5 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD8FCB9770FDCF5FBC6" author="Evans" box="[838,1003,1061,1085]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Distinguished from its relatives by a combination of the following characters (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD8FD30776FDC56FBA5" author="Bell" box="[719,840,1093,1118]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref26637" refString="Bell, E. L. 1941. New species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1125: 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1941">Bell 1941</bibRefCitation>
). Antennae about 2/3 of costa in length, male no secondary sexual characters, wings unmarked dark brown above with shiny green hair-like scales in tornal area of hindwing (and on body), with cream spots below: on hindwing near its middle plus diffuse cream area in distal half of CuA 
<subScript id="17A39A717E54FFD8FDB8779CDD4EFB3F" attach="left" box="[583,592,1206,1220]" fontSize="6" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">2</subScript>
-1A+2A cell, small spots on hindwing in discal cell and as a postdiscal row in each cell between veins M 
<subScript id="17A39A717E54FFD8FDB077FCDD46FB1F" attach="left" box="[591,600,1238,1252]" fontSize="6" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">2</subScript>
and 1A+2A. Male genitalia (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E54FFD8FC1C77EDDB47FB24" author="Bell" box="[995,1113,1223,1247]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref26637" refString="Bell, E. L. 1941. New species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1125: 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1941">Bell 1941</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3 for illustration) with uncus deeply divided, arms long (only slightly shorter than tegumen), parallel, near each other, penis widening terminally (nearly as wide as valva), bulky, with terminal spikes, valva nearly rectangular, sacculus without processes, harpe short (shorter than 1/3 of valva), angular, with a stout tooth pointed dorsad, separated from ampulla by a narrow notch. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly2874.22.9:G1030A, aly3512.12.2:T234C, aly 
<date id="FF99BEF47E54FFD8FC807643DCF2FA7A" box="[895,1004,1385,1409]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" value="2811-06-01">2811.6.1</date>
:T166C, aly1139.93.1:C452C (not G), aly862.12.2:A1755A (not C), aly5021.5.1:G1325G (not C), aly537.7.1:A181A (not G), aly2012.14.2:T317T (not C), aly577.34.1:A485A (not T).
</paragraph>
